crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a comprehensive information stealer and spyware. It establishes persistence through scheduled tasks (schtasks.exe) and registry modifications (Run keys, Winlogon Userinit). It implements keylogging using low-level keyboard hooks (SetWindowsHookExA), monitors the clipboard for text and images, and performs periodic screen/active window captures. Furthermore, it targets browser credentials from Google Chrome and Mozilla Firefox, decrypting them using CryptUnprotectData. For data exfiltration and updates, it leverages bitsadmin.exe for UPLOAD/DOWNLOAD operations. Evasion tactics include monitoring for Task Manager to temporarily disable hooks and terminating specific processes like taskkill.exe.
